    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.47-49_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="authorial">1</fw>
                <fw type="curatorial">47</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    36 <hi rend="caps">MEON. RD
                    BOSCOMBE.E.
                    BOURNEMOUTH 
                    HANTS
                    GT. BRITAIN.</hi>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt.</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I hope you do not mind me writing to you but I have recently read your book. "Eagle Voice", which I found very interesting. In fact I found It so very interesting that I read it 3 times</p>
                
                <p>I have been very interested and fond of the Indians now for some time and I feel very sorry for the true blooded Indian who is shut up In a reservation.</p>
                
                <p>Over here in this country it is impossible to collect any of the articles (war bonnets - Hatchets - pipes - feathers etc.) which I wish to obtain and I wondered If you could suggest any way that I could
               
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.47-49_0002"/>
               
                <fw type="curatorial">48</fw>
                    
                    collect some as it isn't much fun pretending.</p>
                
                <p>Although I'm past the age of playing "cowboys and Indians" I am still very fond of the Indians and the boys at my school say that Indians don't exist anymore but I am sure they do. I have made a breech clout and some leggings from instructions out of an old book. and I have bought a "reasonably" realistic head gear. and I enjoy very much dressing up in them and I have made a totem (not a very good one).</p>
                
                <p>Please don't reply If you are to<sic>too</sic> busy. Thankyou<sic>Thank you</sic>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours sincerely.</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Anthony Potter</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
